Product Requirements Document (PRD)
Project Name: Nexus-V
Theme: Smart Mobility & Digital Infrastructure
Document Status: MVP Draft (Hackathon Version)

1. Executive Summary
The Problem: Automotive services (washing, repairing, EV charging) suffer from high information asymmetry, resulting in wasted time, hidden costs, and "charge anxiety" for drivers.
The Solution: Nexus-V is a unified, real-time platform that connects drivers to service providers. It replaces verbal guesswork with a data-driven "Smart Experience" featuring live queues, mandatory digital proof for repairs, and real-time EV slot booking.
The Goal: Deliver a working prototype demonstrating the real-time sync between a customer app and a partner dashboard across three service verticals.

2. Target Personas
Persona A: The Modern Driver (End User)

Needs: Transparency in pricing, zero physical waiting time, guaranteed EV charging availability.

Pain Points: Sitting in wash queues, getting scammed by mechanics, driving to broken/occupied EV chargers.

Persona B: The Service Partner (Garage/Wash/EV Owner)

Needs: Steady customer flow, dispute-free transactions, easy-to-use digital management tools.

Pain Points: Idle service bays, customers arguing over bills, phone constantly ringing for updates.

3. Core Features & User Stories (MVP Scope)
Module 1: The Zero-Wait Wash (Live Queue System)
Objective: Eliminate physical waiting lines at car washes.

User Story (Driver): As a driver, I want to see the live queue status of nearby car washes so I can join the line remotely and arrive exactly when it’s my turn.

User Story (Partner): As a wash owner, I want a dashboard to update the status of cars (e.g., "Washing," "Finished") so the queue advances automatically for incoming customers.

MVP Requirements:

Map/List view of nearby car washes with a live "Cars Ahead" counter.

"Join Queue" button with an estimated time of arrival (ETA) calculation.

Partner toggle to mark a bay as "Free" or "Occupied."

Module 2: Verifiable Repairs (The Trust Engine)
Objective: Eliminate unauthorized mechanic upcharges through digital proof.

User Story (Partner): As a mechanic, I want to upload a photo of a damaged part and a price quote so the customer can review it remotely.

User Story (Driver): As a driver, I want to receive a push notification with photographic proof of new damage, allowing me to click "Approve" or "Reject" before work continues.

MVP Requirements:

Partner portal interface for uploading images/videos and inputting a quote.

Basic image validation (ensuring an image is actually attached).

Customer interface showing the image, description, and an "Approve/Reject" state toggle.

Immutable logging of the approved quote to prevent end-of-service disputes.

Module 3: Guaranteed EV Charging (Real-Time Booking)
Objective: Eliminate "Charge Anxiety" by securing functional charging slots.

User Story (Driver): As an EV owner, I want to see which chargers are currently functioning and available, and reserve one for 15 minutes while I drive there.

User Story (System): As the backend system, I need to instantly update a charger's status to "Red/Offline" if it is booked or reported broken.

MVP Requirements:

Status indicators for chargers: Green (Available), Yellow (Reserved), Red (Occupied/Offline).

A 15-minute countdown timer upon reservation; if the user doesn't check-in, the slot returns to Green.

4. Non-Functional Requirements (NFRs)
Real-Time Latency: Queue updates and approval notifications must reflect on the client side in under 2 seconds (crucial for the live demo).

Cross-Platform UI: The customer-facing side should look and feel like a native mobile experience (even if built as a responsive web app for the hackathon).

Reliability (Hackathon Context): The backend must gracefully handle concurrent requests so the demo doesn't crash when multiple judges test it simultaneously.

5. Out of Scope (Post-Hackathon Roadmap)
Do not build these for the hackathon, but mention them in the pitch as future scalability.

Integration with actual EV hardware APIs (OCPP).

Complex payment gateway integrations (use dummy escrow buttons for the demo).

AI-based automated damage detection (keep the image verification simple or simulated for now).